title: COVID_01_39y_male_NonICU
characteristics_ch1.17: associated controlled-vocabulary terms: DOID:0080600 UBERON:0003101 NCIT:C70909 CL:0000738 NCIT:C12529
extract_protocol_ch1: 10mL of whole blood collected from patients was filtered and RNA was isolated using LeukoLOCK Total RNA Isolation System.
extract_protocol_ch1.1: TruSeq Stranded mRNA Library prep. Libraries were standardized to 2nM. Paired-end 2x50bp sequencing, using standard SBS chemistry (v3) on an Illumina NovaSeq6000 sequencer.
data_processing: Basecalling via the standard Illumina Pipeline, version 1.8.2.
data_processing.1: Trimming/Filtering for adapters and low quality via custom algorithm
data_processing.2: Expression estimates via RSEM v1.3.0 under Python 2.7.15, using bowtie2-2.3.4.1. Executed command: rsem-calculate-expression --no-qualities --bowtie2 --bowtie2-k 200 --bowtie2-sensitivity-level sensitive --seed-length 20 --keep-intermediate-files --no-bam-output --paired-end [r1.fa.gz] [r2.fa.gz] [hg38 bowtie reference]
data_processing.4: Supplementary_files_format_and_content: tab-delimited expression estimates, including non-normalized Expected Counts (EC), and normalized Transcripts Per Million (TPM)

extract_protocol_ch1: 10mL of whole blood collected from patients was filtered and RNA was isolated using LeukoLOCK Total RNA Isolation System.
extract_protocol_ch1.1: TruSeq Stranded mRNA Library prep. Libraries were standardized to 2nM. Paired-end 2x50bp sequencing, using standard SBS chemistry (v3) on an Illumina NovaSeq6000 sequencer.
data_processing: Basecalling via the standard Illumina Pipeline, version 1.8.2.
data_processing.1: Trimming/Filtering for adapters and low quality via custom algorithm

Executed command: rsem-calculate-expression --no-qualities --bowtie2 --bowtie2-k 200 --bowtie2-sensitivity-level sensitive --seed-length 20 --keep-intermediate-files --no-bam-output --paired-end [r1.fa.gz] [r2.fa.gz] [hg38 bowtie reference]
data_processing.4: Supplementary_files_format_and_content: tab-delimited expression estimates, including non-normalized Expected Counts (EC), and normalized Transcripts Per Million (TPM)
